{
  "stem": "18770.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 265.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I'm so cool, I didn't even ask.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I go, yeah, well, yeah, sure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I'll come down.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It turns out to be Josh Logan.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And on the basis of a script that he's read, I'm hired to write a screenplay for a major film.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so my writing career begins.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you're living in New York?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Your children are growing up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Children are growing up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother is living in New York.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My aunts and uncles are still living there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister, her kids.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, one of the things I want to say about family life, because we've been doing so much about the war, is I remember once seeing an interview with the Taviani-- is that what they're called-- brothers, the two Italian filmmakers.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they said horrible as World War II was-- and they lived in Italy, where so many people were killed in the partisan wars and everything.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They said in a way, for all the terrors of it, it was a very vibrant time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They said it was like an age-- I don't they use the word of gold, but one of the more precious metals.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they said and what followed it is like the age of lead.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And while I can't make exactly that comparison in my life, there is no question that there is a vibrancy to the war and to those war years and the closeness of the family and, you know, the things-- without romanticizing, because a lot of shit is going down, but that later, of course, dissipates.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The family, and, you know, the older people begin to die off.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The family spreads out.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
